<h1><span id="Levitsky_Attack_or_Queen.27s_Bishop_Attack"></span><span id="Levitsky_Attack_or_Queen's_Bishop_Attack">Levitsky Attack or Queen's Bishop Attack</span></h1>
<h3><span id="2._Bg5">2. Bg5</span></h3>
<p>Bg5 is an immediate attack by white, in hopes of slowing black's development via pinning the pawn on e7. This position can be negated by black developing Nf6, or a pawn move f6. usually, the bishop cannot remain in its position for long, necessitating a loss of tempo.
